Date: Wed, 28 May 2014 19:12:13 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 0562/1369] drm/i915: Don't WARN about ring idle bit on gen2
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

commit de8f0a5016c8a0665ec2a55ed0187bad886c7dab upstream.

Gen2 doesn't have the ring idle/stop bits in the SCPD/MI_MODE register,
so don't go spewing warnings about the state of those bits.

Signed-off-by: Ville Syrjälä <ville.syrjala@linux.intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Chris Wilson <chris@chris-wilson.co.uk>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c
index d0c596e..7add7ee 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c
@@ -1497,7 +1497,7 @@ void intel_cleanup_ring_buffer(struct intel_engine_cs *ring)
 		return;
 
 	intel_stop_ring_buffer(ring);
-	WARN_ON((I915_READ_MODE(ring) & MODE_IDLE) == 0);
+	WARN_ON(!IS_GEN2(ring->dev) && (I915_READ_MODE(ring) & MODE_IDLE) == 0);
 
 	iounmap(ringbuf->virtual_start);
 
